    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but what about people who say the deterrence argument is important? like, if someone thinks that harsher sentences are the most direct way to stop crime, are they just objectively wrong about the science or is it just a different perspective? it feels like you're saying the \"evidence-based\" way is the only valid one.",
