      "content": "The deterrence argument is a deeply ingrained, yet scientifically challenged, perspective in criminal justice. While it represents a valid philosophical viewpoint—that fear of punishment is a primary control—it often fails to account for underlying social drivers of crime. Rather than being \"objectively wrong,\" it represents a different paradigm that academic research has shown to be less effective than comprehensive, root-cause interventions.",
